🧠 EXECUTION LAYER SYSTEM
Authoritative Execution Pattern for Record View Engine
🔷 0. PURPOSE

The Execution Layer is not a single layer.

It is the coordinated flow across layers that governs how all system mutations, workflows, and state transitions occur.

It ensures:

✅ UI never mutates state directly
✅ Controller governs all client-side intent
✅ Application is the only mutation boundary
✅ Domain is the only rule authority
✅ Workers execute async logic safely
✅ System always resolves to an authoritative server snapshot
🔷 1. CORE PRINCIPLE

🔥 Execution is always Controller-driven, Application-committed, and Server-authoritative

This means:

UI triggers intent
Controller governs execution
Transport validates + routes
Application executes mutation
Domain enforces rules
Data persists
Workers process async
Controller reconciles
🔷 2. THE CANONICAL EXECUTION FLOW
🧩 End-to-End Flow
UI Interaction
    ↓
Controller Action (governed)
    ↓
Transport Request (validated + authorized)
    ↓
Application Execution (transaction boundary)
    ↓
Domain Rules Applied
    ↓
Data Persistence (DB)
    ↓
Outbox Event (optional)
    ↓
Worker Execution (async)
    ↓
Authoritative Snapshot Returned
    ↓
Controller Reconciliation
    ↓
UI Updated (final truth)

This is non-optional — every execution path must follow this.

🔷 3. LAYER RESPONSIBILITIES IN EXECUTION
🎨 UI LAYER — Intent Only
Captures user actions (edit, save, trigger workflow)
Displays state (dirty, saving, success, error)
NEVER:
mutates server state
applies business logic

👉 UI is input + display only

🎮 CONTROLLER LAYER — Execution Governor

The Controller is the entry point of execution.

Responsibilities
Owns draft state
Tracks dirty state
Decides when execution is allowed
Triggers mutations
Handles responses
Reconciles state
Critical Rule

🔥 No execution occurs without the controller

Example
sectionController.save():
  if (!dirty) return

  sendMutation(payload)
  await response

  replaceLocalState(snapshot)
  clearDirty()
🌐 TRANSPORT LAYER — Execution Gate
Responsibilities
Validate request shape
Enforce auth
Enforce idempotency keys
Normalize errors
Route to application
Critical Rule

🔥 Transport does not execute logic — it protects execution

⚙️ APPLICATION LAYER — Execution Engine

This is where execution actually happens.

Responsibilities
Defines transaction boundary
Coordinates use case
Calls domain logic
Writes all state changes
Writes outbox events
Guarantees idempotency
Critical Rule

🔥 ALL SYSTEM MUTATIONS HAPPEN HERE

🧠 DOMAIN LAYER — Execution Authority
Responsibilities
Validates invariants
Applies business rules
Determines outcomes
Calculates system state
Critical Rule

❗ Domain decides WHAT is valid — not how it is persisted

🗄️ DATA LAYER — Execution Persistence
Executes queries
Applies locking if needed
Ensures consistency
⚙️ INFRA (WORKERS) — Deferred Execution
Responsibilities
Executes async workflows
Retries safely
Applies domain logic in background
Updates system state
Triggered by
Application layer via outbox
🔷 4. EXECUTION TYPES (SYSTEM-WIDE)

All executions fall into one of these categories:

💾 1. SYNCHRONOUS MUTATION (Section Save)

Example: Save Material Section

Flow:

Controller.save()
→ Transport (PATCH /section)
→ Application (transaction)
→ Domain validation
→ DB writes
→ Snapshot returned
→ Controller replaces state

🔑 Output:

Immediate authoritative snapshot
⚙️ 2. ASYNC WORKFLOW EXECUTION

Example: Auto Allocation

Flow:

Controller.trigger()
→ Transport
→ Application writes outbox
→ Worker picks job
→ Domain logic executes
→ DB updated
→ Controller polling detects completion
→ Controller refreshes snapshot

🔑 Output:

Eventually consistent → reconciled to snapshot
🔁 3. RECONCILIATION EXECUTION

Occurs when:

Save completes
Worker completes
External update detected

Controller rules:

State	Behavior
Clean	Auto apply snapshot
Dirty	Block overwrite
Worker complete	Force refresh

👉 Defined in your system as reconciliation behavior

🔷 5. CONTROLLER RECONCILIATION (CRITICAL)

The controller is responsible for closing the execution loop.

Responsibilities
Replace local state with server snapshot
Clear dirty flags
Resolve conflicts
Trigger UI updates
Critical Rule

🔥 Server state always wins

🔷 6. AUTHORITATIVE SNAPSHOT MODEL

Every execution must return or resolve to:

{
  data: FullRecordSnapshot,
  revision: updatedAt,
  status: success | error,
}
Rules
Partial updates are NOT trusted
UI state must be replaced, not patched
Snapshot is the single source of truth
🔷 7. IDEMPOTENT EXECUTION GUARANTEE

All execution paths must be safe to repeat.

Enforced In:
Transport (idempotency keys)
Application (dedupe logic)
Infra (job deduplication)
Guarantees
No duplicate mutations
No duplicate jobs
Safe retries
🔷 8. ERROR EXECUTION FLOW
Domain → throws rule error
→ Application catches/classifies
→ Transport normalizes
→ Controller receives
→ UI displays (section-scoped)
Rules
Errors must be:
deterministic
scoped (section-level)
user-actionable
🔷 9. EXECUTION INVARIANTS (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

These must NEVER be violated:

1. Controller-Governed Execution
No direct API calls from UI
2. Application-Only Mutations
No DB writes outside application layer
3. Domain-Only Business Logic
No rules in controller or UI
4. Snapshot Authority
Server response replaces client state
5. Section as Execution Unit
All execution scoped to a section
6. Idempotent by Default
All actions safe to retry
7. Async = Outbox + Worker Only
No direct background execution from request
